  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally involves financial transactions designed to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money. Key legal definitions typically include:\n\n1. Basic components:\n- Concealing the source of illicit funds\n- Transforming illegal money into seemingly legitimate assets\n- Disguising the true ownership of funds\n\n2. Three primary stages:\n- Placement: Initially introducing illegal funds into financial system\n- Layering: Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure origin\n- Integration: Making laundered funds appear legitimate\n\n3. Legal jurisdictions vary, but most definitions involve:\n- Knowingly processing criminal proceeds\n- Attempting to make illegal funds appear legal\n- Engaging in financial transactions to hide criminal origins\n\n4. Common legal criteria:\n- Intent to conceal criminal proceeds\n- Substantial financial movements\n- Knowledge of funds' illegal source\n\n5. Typical predicate crimes:\n- Drug trafficking\n- Fraud\n- Organized crime\n- Corruption\n- Terrorist financing\n\nSpecific details can differ between countries, but these represent general legal frameworks for understanding money laundering definitions.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
